# Contributor: Sheila Aman <sheila@vulpine.house>
# Maintainer: Natanael Copa <ncopa@alpinelinux.org>
#
# --- Nexus Q (steelhead) local override of Alpine's main/python3 --------------
# Alpine's stock python3-3.14.5-r2 SIGSEGVs on armv7 (Cortex-A9) ON THE DEVICE --
# `python3 -S -c ''` returns rc 139 -- taking down every python consumer
# (sleep-inhibitor.service, onboard, blueman-applet).
#
# This rebuild (r5) drops LTO + PGO at a higher pkgrel so it supersedes Alpine's
# -r2 in the rootfs. (PGO also cannot run in our qemu armv7 build at all -- it would
# execute an instrumented interpreter under qemu.) It keeps stock -O2.
#
# !!! ROOT CAUSE (settled 2026-06-28): the on-device SIGSEGV was NOT a build, compiler,
# or CPython bug -- it was a DEPLOYMENT bug in the FLASH step. raw2simg.py used to mark
# all-zero blocks as fastboot DONT_CARE chunks (skipped on write); the device's U-Boot
# does not pre-erase userdata, so those skipped blocks kept STALE prior-flash garbage,
# which showed through libpython's should-be-zero .PyRuntime/.data.rel.ro and made
# Py_Initialize deref a wild type-index -> SIGSEGV. The BUILT apk was always clean; the
# corruption appeared only AFTER flashing. Fixed in raw2simg.py (now writes every block
# RAW -> byte-exact flash). Verified on hardware: a clean bfd build, flashed correctly,
# gives `python3 -S -c ''` rc 0.
#
# A qemu-user "linker mmap zero-fill corrupts the build" theory was investigated and
# DID NOT REPRODUCE: 6 independent default-linker (bfd) builds were all integrity-clean
# and one ran rc 0 on-device. The gold-linker workaround (-fuse-ld=gold
# -Wl,--no-mmap-output-file) was therefore found UNNECESSARY and DROPPED. The
# deterministic build-integrity gate + rebuild loop in docker-build.sh Phase 7d stays
# as the safety net -- it catches zero-region corruption from ANY source before an apk
# can ship -- and the Phase 10 ship gate re-checks the installed rootfs. ALWAYS still
# validate `python3 -S -c ''` ON THE DEVICE.
# See docs/2026-06-28-session-findings.md, the sparse-dontcare-stale-emmc-corrupts-flash
# and qemu-user-corrupts-armv7-binaries notes.
#
# DISPROVEN along the way (do NOT re-tread): LTO/PGO (r3 dropped both, still crashed),
# LDREXD alignment, TLSDESC, optimization level, and the gold/qemu build theory -- none
# were the cause; the cause was the flash step above.
#
# One further deviation from Alpine's stock APKBUILD: the makedepends no longer
# carries the `!gettext-dev` conflict token. abuild understands `!pkg` (ensure it
# is NOT installed), but pmbootstrap pre-installs makedepends with its own apk
# wrapper, which rejects any `!`-prefixed entry ("packages with '!' are not
# supported!") -- so Phase 7d cannot build python3 with it present. The token is a
# no-op guard here anyway: nothing in this makedepends closure pulls gettext-dev,
# and musl-libintl is listed explicitly, so the build result is unchanged.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pkgname=python3
# python3-extra's pkgver needs to be synchronized with this.
pkgver=3.14.5
_basever="${pkgver%.*}"
pkgrel=5
pkgdesc="High-level scripting language"
url="https://www.python.org/"
arch="all"
license="PSF-2.0"
# pyc0 comes last because the files are named without a unique substring
subpackages="
	$pkgname-dbg
	$pkgname-dev
	$pkgname-doc
	$pkgname-idle::noarch
	$pkgname-tests::noarch
	$pkgname-pyc:_default_pyc
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc2
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc1
	$pkgname-pycache-pyc0
	pyc:_pyc_meta:noarch
	"
depends="libssl3>=3.3.0"
makedepends="
	bluez-headers
	bzip2-dev
	expat-dev
	libffi-dev
	linux-headers
	mpdecimal-dev
	musl-libintl
	ncurses-dev
	openssl-dev
	readline-dev
	sqlite-dev
	tcl-dev
	xz-dev
	zlib-dev
	"
source="https://www.python.org/ftp/python/$pkgver/Python-$pkgver.tar.xz
	idle.desktop
	externally-managed
	musl-find_library.patch
	s390x-c-stack-size.patch
	"
# net: the source tarball is fetched during build.
# !check: skip the upstream test suite -- it is extremely slow and can hang under
# qemu armv7 emulation; we gate correctness on `python3 -S -c ''` (rc 0) instead.
options="net !check" # Required for tests
builddir="$srcdir/Python-$pkgver"

